President Biden and his administration prioritize securing America's supply chains. They welcome Samsung's announcement of building a new semiconductor facility in Texas, which will help protect supply chains, revitalize manufacturing, and create jobs. The administration has been working with Congress, allies, partners, and the private sector to increase semiconductor manufacturing capacity and prevent future shortages. The announcement is a result of ongoing efforts, including engagement with Samsung and President Moon of South Korea. The administration aims to ensure America remains innovative and productive by investing in manufacturing and technology to stimulate economic growth, support the middle class, and enhance long-term competitiveness.